						<summary>

						<p>Second face of the pillar (No. 1) in the main shrine of Bhōgēśvarasvamin temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">14th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This tri-lingual record in Kannada, Nagari and Tamil scripts refers to the obeisance of Vibhūti-Guro, disciple of Guru Panḍitārādhya who is described as Dāsa-Śrī.</p>						

						</summary>
